            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once slightly softened, add your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>drained</strong> <strong>cannellini beans </strong>with 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong>, give everything a good mix up and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [350ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> with your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong> and <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Add 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]<strong> </span>sugar</strong>, mix everything together and cook for 5-6 min or until the sauce has thickened – these are your <strong>homemade cheesy beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-4-1688738025426-x200.jpg",
